ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was one of the most fantastic courses I've taken at Yale! I had no idea how much I did not know about superconductivity. The course was well structured, starting with a basic overview of the phenomena of superconductivity, moving to Ginzberg-Landau theory to solve some simple problems, learning about the theory and applications of Josephson junctions, and finally ending with BCS theory and some great guest lectures. Professor Prober really knows this subject and is a fantastic physics lecturer with a very intuitive style.
